             Lyapunov exponent $\lambda_L$; establishes that $\lambda_L$ is
             bounded by the time-averaged subsystem QFI. Shows universal
             amplification of QFI near quantum phase transitions via
             imaginary-time correlators. Relevant for DS-P10: supports
             independence of $c$ (finite-size scaling exponent operating on $N$)
             and $\lambda_L$ (temporal rate operating on $t$) as variables
             determined by the same underlying dynamics but in distinct spaces.
             Tripathy and Deffner are at UMBC; Deffner is arXiv endorser contact.}}
